    "narrative": "For today's slate, **Cal Raleigh** (71.30) stands as our premier offensive anchor. His matchup against Liberatore is ideal; he benefits from a massive 10% boost due to the opponent's pitching profile and an additional 8% lift from hitting in the two-hole, cementing him as our \"Strong\" start of the day. **Geraldo Perdomo** (68.05) also commands attention as an elite play, largely driven by a favorable matchup against M\u00e1rquez and a 10% bump for leading off. While **Bryson Stott** (66.12) and **Jonathan Aranda** (65.19) occupy the next tier, both provide high-efficiency returns fueled by strong platoon advantages against Elder and Ober, respectively. These players form the core of our strategy to maximize run production against middle-tier starters.\n\nRisk management dictates our approach at the margins. **Taylor Ward** (59.46) and **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez** (59.41) are must-starts despite their matchups against elite arms like Crochet and Gausman, respectively, as their high-order placement and park factors preserve their floor. The most difficult bench decision involved **Jeremiah Jackson** (43.63), who remains on the pine despite a park factor boost; ultimately, the high projected efficiency of our starting outfielders relative to his platoon disadvantage against Crochet kept him on the bench. Conversely, **Masyn Winn** (39.65) was excluded entirely for falling below our 40-point efficiency floor, a necessary discipline to preserve our game caps. Watch **Daulton Varsho** closely; despite his base projection, his score is depressed by a negative platoon shift against Cantillo and a sub-50 total, marking him as a high-risk play today.",
